node.text:
Explorer/Activist Johan Ernst Nilson. Nilson has climbed the Seven Summits (and many other peaks), visited 178 countries and some of the most remote places on Earth, and he is in the Guinness Book of World Records for his Three Poles Challenge Expedition. His travels and experiences have allowed him to see climate change and its consequences first hand, and now Nilson is an activist for change, leading people on expeditions, giving talks, and making films about the environment.

The Astronomia Everest project started with renowned Swedish explorer and environmental activist @johanernst taking an Astronomia Tourbillon with him on an expedition to the Himalayas.
"I wore the regular Astronomia Tourbillon on my last climb to the Himalayas, where I went up to 6,200 meters (almost 20,000 feet), in -30 C degree, extreme conditions," Nilson says. "You would think that such a complicated watch would be delicate and fragile, but it isn't, and it performed perfectly in all conditions. I used it climbing up ice walls, with my ice ax, banging it against rock and ice and it held up extremely well.”

Explorer/Activist Johan Ernst Nilson. Nilson has climbed the Seven Summits (and many other peaks), visited 178 countries and some of the most remote places on Earth, and he is in the Guinness Book of World Records for his Three Poles Challenge Expedition. His travels and experiences have allowed him to see climate change and its consequences first hand, and now Nilson is an activist for change, leading people on expeditions, giving talks, and making films about the environment.

node.text:
Push the right-hand crown of the incredible BUGATTI Chiron Tourbillon and the engine comes to life – the crankshaft turns and the 16 pistons pump up and down, just like BUGATTI’S iconic W16 engine. Two “turbochargers” on the side of the engine block spin while the engine runs, adding to the visual impact.
Incredible to see and unbelievably complicated to realize (the movement is comprised of 578 components), the BUGATTI Chiron Tourbillon timepiece seamlessly marries engines and watches – something no other watchmaker has done before.

The Astronomia Everest project started with renowned Swedish explorer and environmental activist @johanernst taking an Astronomia Tourbillon with him on an expedition to the Himalayas.
"I wore the regular Astronomia Tourbillon on my last climb to the Himalayas, where I went up to 6,200 meters (almost 20,000 feet), in -30 C degree, extreme conditions," Nilson says. "You would think that such a complicated watch would be delicate and fragile, but it isn't, and it performed perfectly in all conditions. I used it climbing up ice walls, with my ice ax, banging it against rock and ice and it held up extremely well.”

Explorer/Activist Johan Ernst Nilson. Nilson has climbed the Seven Summits (and many other peaks), visited 178 countries and some of the most remote places on Earth, and he is in the Guinness Book of World Records for his Three Poles Challenge Expedition. His travels and experiences have allowed him to see climate change and its consequences first hand, and now Nilson is an activist for change, leading people on expeditions, giving talks, and making films about the environment.

Now with the face of Marlon Brando, the Opera Godfather Minute Repeater uses two hammers to strike exposed circular gongs to sound out the hours, the quarters of hours, and the minutes. In the Opera Godfather Minute Repeater, the gongs circle above the dial, visible through the large sapphire crystal and rose gold case. This voluminous case enhances the clarity, tone, and richness of the sound of the gongs.

In the world of watchmaking, the presence of a tourbillon in a watch’s movement places the piece among the elite. @JacobandCo’s Twin Turbo Furious 300+ sets itself apart from this rarified group, incorporating two accelerated triple axis tourbillons into its striking design. The tourbillons work to compensate for the effects of gravity on the precision of the movement.⠀ ⠀
⠀
Even the case of the Twin Turbo Furious Bugatti 300+ is super complicated – made of forged carbon, with a titanium core to ensure water resistance - the case alone is comprised of 88 parts. The grand complication movement is made up of 832 individual parts – incredible to consider that many parts coming together, and amazing to see in action.⠀

Jacob & Co. created a one-of-a-kind bejeweled skateboard pendant for Virgil Abloh. The 18K yellow gold piece was produced over a 10-week period by the luxury brand for the famed American menswear designer. 

It has highly polished spinning 18k gold wheels and a textured 18k gold back of the board paved in yellow diamonds. This is one example of Jacob & Co.’s ability to create customized bespoke jewels.

node.text:
Making a Jacob & Co. custom creation requires multiple steps. American designer, Virgil Abloh, drafted a one-of-a-kind 18k yellow gold and yellow diamond pavé skateboard. Making the object come to life required the work of master artisans. 

A goldsmith produced the multiple surfaces that range from highly polished spinning 18k gold wheels to a textured back of board. Then a skilled gem setter paved the bottom and sides of the surface with 846 sparkling yellow diamonds totaling 10.53 carats. Master artisans took about 10 weeks to complete the piece.

The Epic X Chrono Baguette Rose Gold Case Green Dial is powered by the caliber JCAA05, a @jacobandco exclusive skeleton automatic chronograph movement. The 260-component movement powers regular timekeeping functions and chronograph functions with a small seconds indicator at 9 o’clock and the minute counter at 3 o’clock in a bi-compax design. 

The chronograph functions are controlled by two pushers (start/stop and reset). The seconds are counted by the central chronograph hand and the minutes are clocked by a right-hand subdial.

If the spinning, rotating colorful floral display of the Fleurs de Jardin Rose Gold Diamond Baguette looks familiar, it’s because it’s the same movement used in the Flying Tourbillon Astronomia watch. 

The caliber JCAM31 is both eye-popping and versatile. It’s three arms are used to hold flowers made of kite-shaped colored gems. The caliber's signature 60-second flying tourbillon with its 18k rose gold butterfly designed cage complements the constantly moving floral scene.

The Fleurs de Jardin Rose Gold Diamond Baguette presents a constantly moving blooming garden made of colorful precious gems. The centerpiece is a round 0.81-carat perfectly spherical tsavorite with the 288-facet Jacob Cut that serves as a pistil resting on 12 kite-shaped diamonds that form petals. Hanging flowers made of kite-shaped multicolored gems make a full revolution clockwise around the dial in 10 minutes, while a tsavorite flower rotates counterclockwise in 60 seconds. 

A mother-of-pearl floral ring carrying 5 multicolored gem flowers makes a counterclockwise revolution in 10 minutes.

The highly polished 42.5mm 18K rose gold case of the Brilliant Pendant timepiece reveals an exquisitely crafted skeletonized anthracite caliber JCAM01 manual winding movement with rose gold engraved bridges, gears and Roman numeral “XII” at 12 o’clock. Surrounding the movement is a bezel paved with 72 round brilliant diamonds. Another 31 round brilliant diamonds cover the crown at 12 o’clock. 

Crystal sapphire on the front dial and caseback provides a full view of the movement. Completing this bejeweled, artistic timepiece is an 18K rose gold chain.
